    "body": "1 line creation:\r\n\r\n```\r\ndf = pd.DataFrame(index=pd.MultiIndex.from_product([stocks,dates]), columns=stocks)\r\n```\r\n\r\nand 1 line insertion\r\n\r\n```\r\ndf.loc['GOOG','MSFT']=spread\r\n```\r\n\r\nof course I have a different order to the index.\r\n\r\nSetting with MI is generally painful.  I've also found it to be fragile and unintuitive.  It is often easiest to swap the index levels so that the index you want has level 0."
