    "created_at": "2018-06-30T10:18:12Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-06-30T10:18:12Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> Whereas for a MultiIndex DataFrame a IndexSlice is required for the index, and then the column is separate:\r\n\r\nMy personal solution is actually to include/import in all my code ``WE = slice(None)`` (where ``WE`` is short for \"whatever\"), and then your\r\n\r\n``df.loc[pandas.IndexSlice[:, 'GOOG'], 'MSFT']``\r\n\r\njust becomes\r\n\r\n``df.loc[(WE, 'GOOG'), 'MSFT']``\r\n\r\nBy the way: the most similar thing to a ``Panel`` in terms of syntax is not really a ``DataFrame`` with a 2-levels ``MultiIndex`` on its ``index``, but rather a ``Series`` with a 3-levels ``MultiIndex`` on its ``index``. There, the above would just become\r\n\r\n``s.loc[:,'GOOG','MSFT']``\r\n\r\nas in the panel case."
